You are an expert front-end developer specializing in interactive UI components. Build a single self-contained HTML file with all CSS and JavaScript inline.

**What to build:** A full-screen before/after website screenshot comparison tool with the following behavior:

**Paste functionality:**
- The user can paste images using `Ctrl+V` anywhere on the page
- The first paste sets the **"Before"** image, the second paste sets the **"After"** image
- Show a clear visual prompt guiding the user to paste each image in order (e.g., "الصق صورة قبل" then "الصق صورة بعد")

**Comparison viewer:**
- Both images fill the entire viewport (100vw × 100vh) — no borders, no scrollbars, full bleed
- A vertical **draggable divider** splits the screen left/right between Before and After
- The divider can be dragged with the mouse from **anywhere on the screen** (not just the handle) — clicking and dragging left/right anywhere updates the split position in real time
- The divider handle should be visually prominent (e.g., a circle with arrows ◀▶)

**Scroll behavior:**
- Scrolling the mouse wheel **up/down** pans both images vertically in sync, simulating scrolling through the full webpage screenshot
- The images should be sized so their **width fills the viewport** and their full height is accessible via this vertical scroll — like scrolling through a real website

**Technical requirements:**
- Pure HTML/CSS/JS — no external libraries or CDN dependencies
- All logic in one file, no build step required
- Smooth drag and scroll transitions
- Works in modern browsers (Chrome/Edge/Firefox)
- Use `object-fit: none` and CSS transforms or `background-position` to handle large tall images correctly so the scroll pans through them naturally